    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-11-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-11-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="168"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d168">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Adams</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1876.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-11-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 17, 1866.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I transmit herewith for your information the copy
                    of a note which, on the 15th instant,<note n="*" xml:id="d168fn1">For enclosure
                        see correspondence with British legation.</note> Sir Frederick Bruce
                    addressed to this department regarding the action of the Canadian authorities in
                    the case of the Fenian prisoners who were concerned in the recent raid against
                    Canada.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis, Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
